abstract_str: __wim__ __delvoye__ began tattooing live pigs in 1997 , before doing it in china where animal welfare laws are more lax . belgian artist claims pigs were spoiled , with locals said to have been amazed at how well they were treated . up to three artists applied tattoo while each pig was under anaesthetic , and carers regularly __moisturised__ skin . but animal rights campaigners claim pigs were suffering unnecessarily and abused for improper commercial gain .
